im and Christian. Instead, mutual influences, interconnections, and communications linked northern Africa and southern Europe, surpassing the differences between the two civilizations. It is time that the history of this region reflects such interdependence.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aEmigration and immigrationxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aEmigration and immigrationxReligious aspectsxChristianity. 0aEmigration and immigrationxReligious aspectsxIslam. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  aMediterranean, Medieval History, Late Antiquity, North Africa, Muslim-Christian Relations, Global History, Cross Cultural Exchange.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978164189267440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781641892674423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781641892674/original  a978-3-11-074335-7  DG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2b2021  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK